# and other production data. They belong only in the approved encrypted
# backup store, never in the repository.
backups/
*.dump
*.dump.gz

# Testing
coverage/
app/test-results/
app/playwright-report/
app/blob-report/
.playwright-cli/
# Browser and end-to-end audit captures can contain account data and
# production-like content. Keep the local evidence, but never commit it.
output/

# Misc
*.tgz
.cache/
.vercel

# Administrator token recovery manifests contain one-time plaintext bearer
# credentials. The CLI also rejects every source checkout/Git worktree, while
# these patterns provide defense in depth against accidental staging.
.iam-admin-token-recovery/
**/.iam-admin-token-recovery/**
iam-admin-token-recovery*.json
**/iam-admin-token-recovery*.json
**/*admin-token-recovery*.json

# WeChat mini-program IDE local config
project.config.json
project.private.config.json

# Ad-hoc analysis scratch (kept local, not committed)
# Background-agent audits drop output at the project root; we sweep
# them into _ai_notes/ before commit. The patterns below catch the
# ones we've seen so they don't slip into a commit accidentally.
_ai_notes/
*_AUDIT.md
*_AUDIT_*.md
*_AUDIT.txt
*_AUDIT_*.txt
*_SUMMARY.md
*_SUMMARY.txt
*_REPORT.md
*_FIXES.md
AUDIT_*.md
AUDIT_*.txt
DESIGN_TOKENS_*.md
DESIGN_TOKENS_*.txt
DESIGN_TOKEN_*.md
DESIGN_SYSTEM_*.md
DARK_MODE_*.md
DARK_MODE_*.txt
IMAGE_ANALYSIS_*.md
IMAGE_RENDERING_*.md
IMAGE_RENDERING_*.txt
PERFORMANCE_*.md
PERFORMANCE_*.txt
UI_*.md
EXPLORATION_*.md
.gstack/

# Memory mirror — docs/memory/*.md is the canonical sync layer for Cowork
# chat memory and must NEVER be ignored, even though some filenames
# accidentally match the audit/design-system patterns above on case-
# insensitive filesystems (Windows). Whitelist explicitly:
!docs/memory/
!docs/memory/**
# Audit deliverables — docs/audit/*.md is the canonical location for
# intentional audit content. The *_AUDIT.md / AUDIT_*.md / *_FIXES.md
# / etc. patterns above were scoped to catch background-agent slop at
# project root, but on case-insensitive filesystems (Windows) they also
# match every intentional audit deliverable in docs/audit/. ~15 existing
# tracked files survive only via index grandfathering; new files are
# silently dropped. Whitelist explicitly (parallels docs/memory/ above):
!docs/audit/
!docs/audit/**
# Dated audit screenshots remain local evidence. They can contain real listing
# photos, account state, or synthetic credentials and must never be published.
docs/audit/evidence/
# Current release-security reports contain deployment-gap and production-state
# detail. Keep them in the private local handoff until the corresponding fixes
# are deployed and a disclosure review explicitly approves publication.
docs/audit/2026-07-17-comprehensive-project-audit.md
docs/audit/2026-07-18-supabase-api-key-compatibility.md
docs/audit/2026-07-19-release-candidate-audit.md

# Supabase CLI runtime state — contains pooler-url with embedded DB
# password and linked-project.json. Must NOT be committed.
supabase/.temp/
